    <p>In the middle-ages the Catholic church decided that people could have their pergatory reduced if they perform good works. This is called a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indulgence"><em>plenary</em> or <em>papal</em> indulgence</a>. What qualifies as a 'good work' you may ask? Well, among other things, donating money to a <span style="text-decoration: line-through">the church</span> a good cause of course!
