        <p>So in the middle-ages the plenary indulgence became a method of extracting money from the faithful in exchange for a reduced sentence in the afterlife. It was a fantastic scam. The sale of salvation became big business until in 1567 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indulgence#Late_medieval_abuses">abuse of the practise</a> was so widespread Pope Pius V was compelled to stop the granting of indulgences for money altogether. So the practise stopped... until now!</p>
        <p>We at @ViewBag.SiteName have brought the practise kicking and screaming into the 21st century. You confess to a sin and we'll suggest some charities to make small donation to. Pick one and donate. Then you will receive a genuine* plenary indulgence in PDF format which you can print out and hang on your wall! Pretty neat huh??</p>
